RACE.FOOTNOTES: PLATINUM PROMISE vied for the lead on the inside, made a bid leaving the turn to shake clear, then dug in the final furlong and held on winning the head bob, driving. MORE RANSOM stalked the pace three wide, dropped to the inside entering the turn, then eased off the inside and came five wide into the drive and weakened, bested rest. HOT FUDGE WARRIOR was off a beat slow, rushed up between rivals to duel for command by the half mile marker, then was between rivals by the quarter pole and weakened. ARROGANTE reared at the start when the gates opened losing the rider, then walked off when caught after the race. There was a STEWARDS INQUIRY concerning the start but after reviewing the replays the race was left as is.
